<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='817843' id='t-817843'>and to avoid brutal language.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='819584' id='t-819584'>So, for example, they might say
&quot;taken from us&quot; rather than &quot;killed.&quot;</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
13:55
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='824187' id='t-824187'>Speaking of which,
it's about time I killed this talk,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='826844' id='t-826844'>but before I do, I just want 
to give you in 30 seconds</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='830052' id='t-830052'>the overarching myth of psychology.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='833423' id='t-833423'>So the myth is that psychology is just
a collection of interesting theories,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='837720' id='t-837720'>all of which say something useful
